    <p product="author developer editor authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">This type of
      WebHelp system can be generated by using the <xref
        href="wh-responsive-output.dita#wh-responsive-output/webhelp_responsive_with_feedback_output"
          ><uicontrol>DITA Map WebHelp Responsive with Feedback</uicontrol> transformation
        scenario</xref> and following the <xref
        href="deploying-webhelp-responsive-feedback.dita#deploying-webhelp-responsive-feedback"
        >instructions for deploying the feedback system</xref>.</p>
    <p product="webhelp">This type of WebHelp system can be generated by using the
        <uicontrol>webhelp-responsive</uicontrol> transformation type in your <xref
        href="dita-webhelp-plugin.dita#dita-webhelp-plugin">DITA to WebHelp script</xref> and
      following the <xref
        href="deploying-webhelp-responsive-feedback.dita#deploying-webhelp-responsive-feedback"
        >instructions for deploying the feedback system</xref>.</p>
    <section id="layout">
      <title>Layout</title>
      <p>The layout of the <b>WebHelp Responsive with Feedback</b> system is platform independent
        and is able to adapt to any screen size. It is highly customizable and relies on a <xref
          href="webhelp_templates_mechanism.dita#webhelp_templates_mechanism">template
          mechanism</xref> that allows you to control the position of various functional <xref
          href="webhelp_template_components.dita#webhelp_template_components">template
          components</xref> to suit your particular requirements. </p>
      <p>You can select from several different styles of layouts (for example, by default, you can
        select either a <i>tiles</i> or <i>tree</i> style of layout). Furthermore, each
        of these layouts include a collection of skins that you can choose from, or you can
        customize your own.</p>
      <p>The <b>WebHelp Responsive with Feedback</b> system also contains a
          <uicontrol>Comments</uicontrol> section at the bottom of the pane. This section is where
        you can interact with users through a comment system. </p>
